<h2>What Is GEO Scoring? The Complete Guide (2026)</h2>
<p>92% of brands are failing at AI search visibility. Not because they ignore it. Because they have no way to measure it.</p>
<p>Traditional SEO has clear metrics. Rankings. Traffic. Click-through rates. You know where you stand. GEO (Generative Engine Optimization) had no equivalent scoring system until recently. Brands optimized blindly, published content, and hoped AI systems would cite them.</p>
<p>GEO scoring changes that. It is a measurement framework that quantifies how visible and citable your content is across AI search platforms like ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews, and Bing Copilot. Instead of guessing, you get a number. A score. A clear target to improve.</p>
<p>The <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2509.10762">GEO-16 research framework</a> analyzed 1,702 AI citations across 1,100 URLs and identified the 16 on-page signals that predict whether AI systems cite your content. That research produced the first empirical connection between page quality signals and AI citation outcomes.</p>
<p>We have published 3,500+ blogs across 70+ industries with a 92% average SEO score. GEO scoring is how we measure and optimize for <a href="/blog/track-ai-search-visibility/">AI search visibility</a>. This guide explains every component.</p>
<p>Here is what you will learn:</p>
