<h2>7 Key GEO Metrics Every Business Should Track</h2>
<p>GEO scoring is the umbrella. Under it sit specific metrics that measure different aspects of AI visibility. Here are the 7 that matter most.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="7 key GEO metrics to track for AI search visibility" src="/images/blog/geo-scoring-7-metrics.webp" /></p>
<h3>1. Citation Frequency</h3>
<p>How often your content gets cited in AI-generated responses for your target queries. This is the GEO equivalent of ranking position in traditional SEO. Track it weekly for your top 20 to 30 target queries across ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Google AI Overviews.</p>
<h3>2. Share of Voice (SoV)</h3>
<p>Your brand's citation frequency divided by total citations for a query set. If 10 brands get cited for "best CRM software" queries and your brand appears in 3 out of 10 responses, your SoV is 30%.</p>
<p>SoV reveals competitive position. A rising SoV means you are gaining ground. A falling SoV means competitors are optimizing faster.</p>
<h3>3. Brand Visibility Score</h3>
<p>A composite metric (0 to 100) showing how prominently your brand appears across all AI platforms for your target keywords. Visibility accounts for citation frequency, citation position (mentioned first vs last), and citation context (recommended vs merely mentioned).</p>
<h3>4. GEO Content Score</h3>
<p>A page-level metric (0 to 100) that quantifies the AI-readiness of a specific piece of content. It combines the 16 GEO pillar scores into a single number. Content scoring above 70 is considered AI-optimized. Below 50 needs structural work.</p>
<p>This is different from your overall brand GEO score. A brand can have some pages scoring 90 and others scoring 20. The page-level score identifies exactly which content needs improvement.</p>
<h3>5. Generative Position</h3>
<p>Where your brand appears in AI-generated lists. When ChatGPT lists "the top 5 SEO tools," being position 1 is dramatically more valuable than position 5. Generative position tracks your placement within these ranked responses.</p>
<h3>6. Query Coverage</h3>
<p>The percentage of relevant queries where your brand appears at all. If you target 100 AI-relevant queries and your brand appears in responses for 35 of them, your query coverage is 35%.</p>
<p>Low query coverage with high citation frequency means you dominate a narrow topic. High coverage with low frequency means broad but shallow visibility.</p>
<h3>7. Fresh Content Citation Velocity</h3>
<p>How quickly newly published content starts getting cited by AI systems. Some content gets cited within days. Other content takes weeks. Faster velocity indicates strong GEO signals that AI systems trust and prioritize.</p>
<p>For a complete measurement setup, read our guide on <a href="/blog/track-ai-search-visibility/">tracking AI search visibility</a>.</p>
