<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>What is a good GEO score?</strong></p>
<p>A normalized GEO score of 0.70 or higher (70 out of 100 on percentage scales) indicates strong AI citation readiness. Pages scoring above this threshold with 12+ of the 16 GEO pillars optimized show substantially higher citation rates across ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Google AI Overviews.</p>
<p><strong>How is GEO scoring different from SEO scoring?</strong></p>
<p>SEO scoring measures Google ranking potential based on keywords, backlinks, and technical health. GEO scoring measures AI citation likelihood based on content structure, schema markup, freshness, entity signals, and crawler access. The two overlap on <a href="/blog/eeat-google-quality-guide/">E-E-A-T</a> and content quality, but GEO adds dimensions that SEO scoring does not cover.</p>
<p><strong>What is the GEO-16 framework?</strong></p>
<p>GEO-16 is a <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2509.10762">research-backed auditing framework</a> with 16 pillars that predict AI citation behavior. It was developed by analyzing 1,702 citations across 1,100 URLs from Brave, Google AI Overviews, and Perplexity. The framework produces a normalized score from 0 to 1 for each page.</p>
<p><strong>Which GEO metric matters most?</strong></p>
<p>Citation frequency is the most direct indicator of GEO success. It measures how often your content gets cited in AI-generated responses for your target queries. Share of Voice is the most important competitive metric, showing your citation frequency relative to competitors.</p>
<p><strong>Can I check my GEO score for free?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Mangools AI Search Grader provides free page-level GEO scoring. Geoptie offers a free GEO Rank Tracker for brand monitoring. You can also run a manual audit using the GEO-16 pillar checklist in this article. Paid tools like Otterly AI and GEOReport.ai provide deeper analysis.</p>
<p><strong>Does improving GEO score also improve SEO?</strong></p>
<p>In most cases, yes. Many GEO improvements (better content structure, schema markup, faster load times, stronger E-E-A-T signals) also benefit traditional Google rankings. The investment is additive. You are not choosing between SEO and GEO. You are building both simultaneously.</p>
